{"title":"The Act","author":{"name":"William Carlos Williams"},"publishDate":"2010-11-25","lines":[{"line":"There were the roses, in the rain. ","stanza":1,"number":1},{"line":"Don’t cut them, I pleaded. ","stanza":1,"number":2},{"line":"They won’t last, she said. ","stanza":1,"number":3},{"line":"But they’re so beautiful ","stanza":1,"number":4},{"line":"where they are. ","stanza":1,"number":5},{"line":"Agh, we were all beautiful once, she said, ","stanza":1,"number":6},{"line":"and cut them and gave them to me ","stanza":1,"number":7},{"line":"in my hand.","stanza":1,"number":8}]}